Several other remarks have been made that are also incorrect. <br>
<br>
We never booked Hate, and therefore never got 'screwed' by Agony. We have never use to calendar to book raids, we consider all mobs/planes/dragons FCFS. No one has ever approached us as to how we see these things, although we have been in the Planes for at least 8 weeks, without ever booking them. So Narya maybe you shoud reread others' posts as well before replying. Nowhere is the word 'reserved' used. He writes 'planned'. <br>
<br>
Baldrik was obvioulsy upset after being harrassed in tells by people he had never met, grouped with, or ever had anything to do with. It is insinuated he has deleted/hacked or tampered with the calendar in some other manner, in the middle of a raid. He logged to check the boards to make sure it wasn't booked, something we usually do, and because he was the first to notice this and take advantage of it, he is immediately made the scapegoat of someone's attempt to disturb the peace of the server.<br>
<br>
We have always gone by the motto FCFS. Vaclav seems to think Baldrik 'changed' tactic mid conversation. Of the 60 odd members of CC, approximately 15 have English as a first language. His grammar, sentence structure etc may not always be perfect, but he did not suddenly decide we were a FFA guild.<br>
<br>
--------------------<br>
<br>
All guilds have silly squables over spawns, you had one of two ways to handle it: a. Be an ass and state that the rules most of the server abides by were below you OR b. Apologize, explain the misunderstanding and try to comply to the rules in the future.<br>
<br>
-------------------------------<br>
<br>
This quote by Vaclav is amusing, as its exactly how I would have felt looked upon the people sending me tells, if I were Baldrik. He was accused of deleting posts based on nothing more than Narya's accusations so far. If it had been explained that a post was deleted and this is why the plane appeared to be unbooked when Baldrik checked, we would probably have come to some sort of agreement. This was not done though. It was insinuated that Baldrik, or someone in Caer Cadarn had deleted a post, so we could enter the plane and point to the calendar as our 'alibi'. <br>
<br>
Come with a little hard proof before you start slagging people off, and threatening with making us the server pariahs.<br>
<br>
Just for the record. We do not use the calendar, we do not recognise it. We believe in FCFS. I am sorry if you feel this will mean the moral fibre of the server will now be ripped apart by us 'forcing' other guilds to adopt this stance as well. It hasn't in the last 8 weeks we have been visiting planes, but that seems to have been missed by certain posters.<br>
<br>
We generally check the boards before going to a plane, and respect the bookings of other guilds, but we have no plans to book them ourselves.<br>
<br>
On a side note, we play and raid 6 to 12 hours ahead of US guilds. If we were to book planes it would mean we either raid US times to coincide with respawns, or US guilds raid 'Euro' times to coincide with respawns after our visits to them. Neither is going to happen. To illustrate.<br>
<br>
CC books Fear for 6 am EST Saturday. To ensure a full respawn, which I presume these booking guilds do, anyone who booked Fear for Friday, must be kill their last mob around 6pm EST, otherwise we are left with a partially respawned plane. This basically means Friday is out of the question for many guilds to raid Fear.Once we had entered Fear, the plane would not begin to respawn until 6pm Saturday, with a full respawn some 4 to 8 hours later. <br>
<br>
Maybe this means sweet FA to anyone. In the end i don't really care. Baldrik was accused of tampering with a public forum. Insted of attempting to implement 'B' in Vaclav's suggestion of how to resolve matters, he resorts to petty insinuations<br>
<br>
In most western countries, including the USA, citizens are considered innocent until proven guilty. All I see here is slander and insinuation.<br>
